    {
      "color": "4",
      "height": 80,
      "id": "b740f535e07ca6df",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "Tablet switch back and forth",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 480,
      "x": -5800,
      "y": -6613
    },
    {
      "height": 278,
      "id": "e5ad857c88cf8a5d",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "- Invert solution requirements (the solution becomes the obstacle, and vice versa)\n- misdirect with red herrings\n- same puzzle, different emphasis\n\nask \"how can this mechanic betray the player's first guess?\"",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 670,
      "x": -5629,
      "y": -6914
    },
    {
      "height": 82,
      "id": "3da759fab97dc361",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "Take a previous concept and \"flip it on its head\"",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 393,
      "x": -5756,
      "y": -7007
    },
    {
      "height": 122,
      "id": "08c088cccb4fe5df",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "Vary the under-the-hood variables. Have weird doors, weird weights, weird implementations of rewire.",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 380,
      "x": -5019,
      "y": -6695
    },
    {
      "height": 153,
      "id": "826b94cdac67d851",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "Invert the on/off input of receiver devices, invert on/off output of output devices",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 260,
      "x": -5019,
      "y": -6884
    },
    {
      "autoResizeHeight": false,
      "color": "4",
      "height": 65,
      "id": "9926a24b8980376b",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "~~Dog + Sprocket Push (Dog in cage)~~",
