      },
      "text": "Abandoned Mall",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 250,
      "x": -2560,
      "y": -2660
    },
    {
      "color": "7",
      "height": 60,
      "id": "b4de2a079a45c944",
      "styleAttributes": {
        "border": null
      },
      "text": "Codec",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 140,
      "x": -2335,
      "y": -2490
    },
    {
      "color": "3",
      "height": 120,
      "id": "9917a100c9f7f31d",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "Construction workers trying to bust down entryway",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 260,
      "x": -2700,
      "y": -2260
    },
    {
      "color": "1",
      "height": 263,
      "id": "bf2e25f18099e1e4",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "Octopus\n- sprocket push 1d\n- bounce\n- weight platform\n- snatcher disable\n- snatcher transport",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 294,
      "x": 196,
      "y": -3763
    },
    {
      "height": 540,
      "id": "bdac5071a14edca3",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "ugly mvp, no fucking detail, no fucking npcs, no fucking extra space\n\nyou are not creating the levels. you are creating a test space exclusively to establish the feel of collecting the items.\n\n- [x] put items in world\n- [x] put gates in world\n",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 480,
      "x": -360,
      "y": -4630
    },
    {
      "height": 100,
      "id": "028324fbf168a586",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "Layout dictated by puzzles",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 300,
      "x": -30,
      "y": -4410
    },
    {
      "file": "Maps/map pallette.png",
      "height": 400,
      "id": "965cbc33e1f18538",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "type": "file",
      "width": 364,
      "x": 2740,
      "y": -1425
    },
    {
      "height": 1062,
      "id": "f07e1f4eec158cc1",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "pushable objects:\n### Puzzle\n- variability based on force applied\n\t- speed of block\n\t\t- frictionless surface, small push = longer time\n\t- time until block comes back\n\t\n- push chunks of puzzles\n- timed paddle wheel\n- rotate room/round platform\n- pushable platform/lift/tram\n- sprocketing against any puzzle door 50 times will break it (for cheaters)\n### Gimmick\n- pully system\n- fence fall down\n- progressive paddle wheel (boost ball style)\n- domino props/enemies\n- push car\n- boat rotor\n- heavy shopping cart\n- fan belt\n- rattle/dislodge most decorations\n- block that slides to a halt\n- balloon game, force of air affects balloon's lift\n- inflating balloon, pushing fragile balloon to goal (full blast pops it)\n- launch water ball",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 740,
      "x": 660,
      "y": -3082
    },
    {
      "height": 150,
      "id": "44cb1d40e3ffbb1b",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "No two sprocket interactable items are the same. The sprocket gun is a tool of spectacle, gimmick, and charm.",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 457,
      "x": 121,
      "y": -2318
    },
    {
      "height": 640,
      "id": "35986926c3f88c67",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "No reason to ever vary the pressure applied by the sprocket gun. Even if it's possible to shoot weaker, there is never an advantage to doing so. Inverting the requirements doesn't solve the problem, either. There is never any reason to go \"middle of the road.\"\nYou need a qualitative difference for different force levels, not quantitative. And there must be a naturally occurring need to select different force levels.\n\nIn that sense, the sprocket gun is identical to a punch or kick.",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 380,
      "x": 1460,
      "y": -2900
    },
    {
      "height": 180,
      "id": "485c44ddace53c5b",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "Good implementations will feature friction or other physical effects (not just being \"turned on\" with a full blast)",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 340,
      "x": 258,
      "y": -2200
    },
    {
      "height": 140,
      "id": "9210e7b85be556c8",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "Bosses are strictly tests of knowledge with more noise added for challenge.",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 292,
      "x": 20,
      "y": -3000
    },
    {
      "height": 90,
      "id": "8f99ee4c815cdaa6",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "Avoid noise outside of bosses.",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 297,
      "x": 280,
      "y": -2920
    },
    {
      "color": "4",
      "height": 60,
      "id": "0b4618d4ad98b9a3",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "Weight Platform Intro",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 412,
      "x": -1036,
      "y": -3630
    },
    {
      "color": "4",
      "height": 60,
      "id": "3f4de4b0643b0dbe",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "Snatcher Transport Intro",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 342,
      "x": -1036,
      "y": -3430
    },
    {
      "color": "2",
      "height": 60,
      "id": "f891b46bd0a846d6",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "[[Breathing Device]]",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 250,
      "x": -200,
      "y": -3460
    },
    {
      "height": 505,
      "id": "bcf76bdb61a14a53",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "new puzzle:\nneeds:\n- snatcher\n- paddle\n- weight platform\n- water level\n\nwhat's my issue? don't know how these could possibly fit together. no obvious layout happening for me. things feel too vague and disconnected.\nwhat will the essence of this puzzle be? what wrinkle will the player be tested on? I feel stressed because \"I have to come up with a puzzle quickly\" but in order to get a decent puzzle going I need to experiment.",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 627,
      "x": 540,
      "y": -3648
    },
    {
      "height": 220,
      "id": "9e180f257321b7d4",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "Need more combination attempts. I should return to my matrix and add my new mechanics to the list",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 356,
      "x": -930,
      "y": -4851
    },
    {
      "height": 320,
      "id": "4ec8c85e607b7e84",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "- [x] Bouncy Skirt Upgrade\n- [x] Sprocket Push\n- [x] Sprocket Nozzle\n- [x] Sprocket Jump\n- [x] Heavy Shoulder Upgrade\n- [x] Tablet Range\n- [x] Metal Boots Tier 2",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 470,
      "x": -830,
      "y": -4520
    },
    {
      "height": 324,
      "id": "053f095bd5a64b5d",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "I'm upset. The discotech has a lot of low quality puzzles and some highly cheesey technical ones\n\nMy initial organization of puzzles is failing. I need better puzzles.",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 340,
      "x": -1036,
      "y": -5125
    },
    {
      "height": 450,
      "id": "efa3a6edbfeeeb7a",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "Skip the puzzle. Come back later. Focus this energy on puzzles that come easily.",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 460,
      "x": 1120,
      "y": -3593
    },
